@startuml sequence_planner_with_rhythm
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Weekend Generation - Planner Applies Daily Rhythm

actor "User / WebJob" as trigger
participant "GenerateWeekendHandler" as gen
participant "WeekendPlanner" as planner
participant "RhythmGate" as gate
participant "NapBlockSeeder" as napseed
participant "CommitmentSeeder" as commitseed
participant "ActivityScheduler" as sched
database "Azure SQL" as sql

trigger -> gen: POST /api/weekends/generate
gen -> sql: Load Family + Members + Commitments\n+ Activities + Restaurants + Events
sql --> gen: rows
gen -> planner: Plan(inputs)\n  OutTheDoorBy=09:00\n  BackHomeBy=20:00\n  Mae: nap 12:30-14:30, home-only
planner -> gate: DayWindow(Saturday)
gate --> planner: (09:00, 20:00)

== Step 1: seed the nap blocks (BEFORE anything else) ==
planner -> napseed: Seed(inputs)
note over napseed
  For each member with NapStart+NapEnd:
   - Emit a locked Downtime block
     on Saturday AND Sunday
   - Title: "{Name}'s nap"
   - Reason: "Daily rhythm: respect nap"
   - 15-min "drive home" buffer added if
     NapNeedsHome AND last block isn't home.
end note
napseed --> planner: [Mae's nap Sat 12:30-14:30 (locked),\n Mae's nap Sun 12:30-14:30 (locked)]

== Step 2: seed locked commitments ==
planner -> commitseed: Seed(inputs)
commitseed --> planner: [Swim Sat 09:00-10:00,\n Church Sun 10:30-11:45]

== Step 3: schedule activities around locks ==
planner -> sched: Schedule(inputs, lockedBlocks)
note over sched
  Constraints applied:
   - StartTime >= OutTheDoorBy
   - EndTime <= BackHomeBy
   - No overlap with any locked block
   - If a nap requires home, avoid
     scheduling drives that end after nap start
end note
sched --> planner: [activities, meals, drives, downtime]

planner -> planner: Merge + sort blocks\nby (Day, StartTime, SortOrder)
planner --> gen: PlannerOutput

gen -> sql: INSERT ItineraryBlocks
sql --> gen: ok
gen --> trigger: 200 OK + WeekendDto

@enduml
